# CODEOWNERS — required-review routing for Ownware's security-sensitive surfaces.
#
# WARNING: GitHub CODEOWNERS uses LAST-match-wins semantics. If you add an
# overlapping rule BELOW the security block, include the security owner on
# that entry too — otherwise you silently remove required security review.
# scripts/check-codeowners.mjs (bun run check:codeowners) guards against this.
#
# Ownware currently has a single maintainer, so every rule points at the same
# handle. The value is the enforced review SURFACE: with branch protection's
# "Require review from Code Owners" enabled, no PR touching these paths can
# merge unseen. When a security team exists, swap the handle for the team —
# never delete rules.

# ── Protect the ownership rules themselves + the leak boundary ──────────────
/.github/CODEOWNERS @tariq659891
/.gitignore @tariq659891
/.gitleaks.toml @tariq659891

